Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top
rack until browned and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Quarter
@mandarin orange{1}(quartered). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Halve
@potato buns{2}(halved).

== Zesty Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the
@Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, half the lime zest, @olive oil{1%tablespoon},
@sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, @Fajita spice blend{1/4%tablespoon}, juice from one lime
wedge, and juice from one mandarin orange wedge. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use all the lime zest, 2 TBSP olive oil, 1 tsp sugar, 1⁄2 tsp
> Fajita Spice Blend, juice from two lime wedges, and juice from two
> mandarin orange wedges.

== Pork Burgers ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, garlic,
remaining Fajita Spice Blend, remaining mustard, @salt{1/2%tsp}, juice from one
lime wedge, juice from one mandarin orange wedge, and pepper. Form into two
patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp of salt, juice from two lime wedges, and juice from
> two mandarin orange wedges. Form four patties instead of two.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties
and cook until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

In the last minute of cooking, top each patty with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup};
cover pan to melt cheese.

Turn off heat; transfer patties to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Assembly ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in the same pan over medium heat. Add buns, cut side
down; toast until golden, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches, using 1 TBSP butter for each
> batch.

Spread bottom and top buns with a thin layer of sauce. Fill buns with patties
and @dill pickle{1}(sliced) slices.

Divide cheeseburgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with any
remaining lime wedges, mandarin orange wedges, and sauce on the side.